   <titles>
      <title>Triangle Inequality for Numbers: Illustration</title>
   </titles>
   <body>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>If <math>
                     <latex>x,y,z\in\RNr</latex>
                  </math>, we have the identity</para.body>
            </para>
            <math.array column="3">
               <row rowspan="1">
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>\Dstnc{x}{z}</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>=</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>\Dstnc{x}{y} + \Dstnc{y}{z}</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
               </row>
            </math.array>
            <para>
               <para.body>called the triangle inequality. This terminology is motivated by the situation in the plane depicted below:</para.body>
            </para>
            <media type="image" active="0" inline="0">
               <img src="ims/TriangleInequalityR2.png"/>
            </media>
            <para>
               <para.body>Here we see three points <math>
                     <latex>P,Q,R</latex>
                  </math> in the plane and, in agreement with everyday experience, the distance from <math>
                     <latex>P</latex>
                  </math> to <math>
                     <latex>R</latex>
                  </math> is less than or equal to the length of the ‘detour’ from <math>
                     <latex>P</latex>
                  </math> to <math>
                     <latex>R</latex>
                  </math> via <math>
                     <latex>Q</latex>
                  </math>.</para.body>
            </para>
         </block.body>
      </block>
